  <p>Masculine anthroponymic proper nouns name male persons, e.g. <m>Seumas</m>
    <en>James</en>, <m>Dòmhnall</m>
    <en>Donald</en>. They are unchanged in the dative case, and are both slenderised and lenited in the genitive, e.g. <m>le Seumas</m>
    <en>with James</en>, <m>taigh Sheumais</m>
    <en>James’ house</en>. <boxlink ref="#masculine_anthroponyms"/></p>
