  <p>Some anthroponymic proper nouns have <strong>diminutive</strong> alternatives, e.g. <m>Seumaidh</m>
    <en>Jimmy</en> and <m>Peigi</m>
    <en>Peggy</en> are diminutive versions of <strong>Seumas</strong> and <strong>Mairead</strong> respectively. <boxlink ref="#diminutive_anthroponyms"/></p>
  <box id="diminutive_anthroponyms">
    <title>diminutive anthroponymic proper nouns</title>
    <p>Diminutive anthroponymic proper nouns are informal, colloquial variants of more official anthroponymic proper nouns used to name people.</p>
    <p>These are declined for case in the same way as other anthroponymic proper nouns.</p>
    <p>Here is a comprehensive list of feminine diminutive anthroponymic proper nouns –</p>
